commit.message:
When moving out of a for loop head, suggest borrowing it

When encountering code like the following, suggest borrowing the for loop
head to avoid moving it into the for loop pattern:

```
fn main() {
    let a = vec![1, 2, 3];
    for i in &a {
        for j in a {
            println!("{} * {} = {}", i, j, i * j);
        }
    }
}
```

